723019f.title: Manhattan: Rockefeller Plaza - 48th Street (West)
723019f.text:
Rockefeller Plaza, (center foreground and
not constructed) from West 48th (left margin)
to 5lst (right margin) Street's, showing the
development of this new midtown center. Prominent
in the middle is the 70-story R.C.A. Building.
To the left and right respectively are R.K.0.
Centre Theatre and the 31-story R.K.O. Building
and the International Music Hall. All of these
structures front on Sixth Avenue on their far sides,
and are viewed westward across Fifth Avenue. The
photographers vantage point is the 40-storied structure,
No. 444 Madison Avenue that is to the rear of Saks
Fifth Avenue Department Store. At the top appears
a glimpse of the North (Hudson) River and its Jersey
shore.
1932
Gift of Rockefeller Center
Publicity Department
